<div id="review_2695431800" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2695431800" />
    <a title="NHC Gonzo Division " class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/84334044-nhc-gonzo-division"><img alt="NHC Gonzo Division " src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1532317285p2/84334044.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2695431800?book_show_action=true">Jan 30, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="NHC Gonzo Division " class="user" itemprop="url" name="NHC Gonzo Division " href="/user/show/84334044-nhc-gonzo-division">NHC Gonzo Division </a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2695431800" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3444224731480802288">I prefer the violent/criminal/druggy side of the Trainspotting franchise with Begbie and Spud, to the sex side with the likes of Juice Terry and Sick Boy, but there was quite a few moments in it that made me laugh out loud! This was the final book by Welsh for me to read, I’ve now read and own every one of his works. His bibliography is 80% pure genius storytelling and incredible characters. If you’ve not read his other books I’d recommend them first, but A Decent Ride is a decent read and was n</span>
  <span id="freeText3444224731480802288" style="display:none">I prefer the violent/criminal/druggy side of the Trainspotting franchise with Begbie and Spud, to the sex side with the likes of Juice Terry and Sick Boy, but there was quite a few moments in it that made me laugh out loud! This was the final book by Welsh for me to read, I’ve now read and own every one of his works. His bibliography is 80% pure genius storytelling and incredible characters. If you’ve not read his other books I’d recommend them first, but A Decent Ride is a decent read and was not disappointing. I noticed a lot of typos in this book, but that’s to be expected I guess with the nightmare of a job it must be to edit all that Scottish slang! I’m desensitised to Welsh’s filth, he failed to shock me in this one, but anyone who isn’t will find some bits shocking... </span>
  <a data-text-id="3444224731480802288" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

